# Risk Assessment Using NIST Cybersecurity Framework

## 📌 Objective
This project demonstrates a basic risk assessment for a fictional company using the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, Recover).

## 🛠 Tools Used
- NIST CSF spreadsheet template (custom Excel file)
- Microsoft Word (for risk report)
- Public data from a fictional or example company (e.g., small IT firm)

## 🔍 Key Findings
- Top risks identified in the Protect function
- Gaps in patch management and access control
- Recommended improvements: implement MFA, patch review cycle

## 📊 Files Included
- Risk-Assessment-Report.pdf
- Risk-Scoring-Matrix.xlsx

## 🧠 What I Learned
- How to apply the NIST CSF in a real-world setting
- Risk identification and mitigation strategies
- Writing an executive risk summary

